## SS 6. Subscribe to Newsletter (After Commenting)

Subscribe after commenting. Click triggers redirect to pledge page — subscription completes on first click. Navigate back immediately (skip interstitials).

**Step 1 — Click topmost Subscribe button on the post page:**

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1000)); var btns = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button')); if (btns.some(b => /subscribed|following/i.test(b.innerText.trim()))) return { alreadySubscribed: true }; var subBtns = btns.filter(b => b.innerText.trim() === 'Subscribe'); if (subBtns.length === 0) return { error: 'no subscribe button' }; var topBtn = subBtns.reduce((best, b) => b.getBoundingClientRect().y < best.getBoundingClientRect().y ? b : best); topBtn.dispatchEvent(new MouseEvent('click', { bubbles: true, cancelable: true })); return { clicked: true }; }"}
ENDJSON
```

**Step 2 — Navigate back to post (skip interstitials):**

The subscribe completes immediately on click. The redirect goes to a pledge page with 4 optional screens. Skip all of them by navigating back:

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/navigate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"url":"{post_url}"}' 2>&1
```

Wait 2s, then verify no Subscribe button remains:

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 2000)); var btns = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button')); var hasSubscribe = btns.some(b => b.innerText.trim() === 'Subscribe'); return { subscribed: !hasSubscribe }; }"}
ENDJSON
```

