## SS 7. Notes Engagement

Navigate to `https://substack.com/notes`, wait 3s:

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000)); var notes = document.querySelectorAll('[class*=\"note\"], article'); return Array.from(notes).slice(0, 10).map(note => { var text = note.innerText; var author = (note.querySelector('a[href*=\"/@\"]') || {}).innerText || ''; var link = note.querySelector('a[href*=\"/note/\"], a[href*=\"/p/\"]'); var url = link ? link.href.split('?')[0] : ''; return { url, author: author.slice(0, 30), preview: text.slice(0, 200) }; }).filter(n => n.url || n.preview.length > 20); }"}
ENDJSON
```

## SS 8. Batch Like Notes (from feed page)

🚨 Notes feed Like buttons do NOT change `aria-label` to "Unlike" after clicking. Verify by checking count increase.

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1000)); var btns = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button')); var likeBtns = btns.filter(b => { var label = (b.getAttribute('aria-label') || '').toLowerCase(); return label === 'like' && b.getBoundingClientRect().width > 0; }); var liked = []; var max = MAX_LIKES_PLACEHOLDER; for (var i = 0; i < likeBtns.length && liked.length < max; i++) { var b = likeBtns[i]; var prevCount = parseInt(b.innerText.trim()) || 0; b.dispatchEvent(new MouseEvent('click', { bubbles: true, cancelable: true })); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 500)); var newCount = parseInt(b.innerText.trim()) || 0; if (newCount > prevCount) { liked.push({ idx: i, prev: prevCount, now: newCount }); } else { b.dispatchEvent(new MouseEvent('click', { bubbles: true, cancelable: true })); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 300)); } } return { liked: liked }; }"}
ENDJSON
```
